# Review of `app.js` — Error Handling, Input Validation & Security

The app is minimal (two GET endpoints, no inputs yet), so most findings are about **missing defensive scaffolding** that you'll want before adding any real routes. Here's a prioritized review.

## 1. Missing global error handling

There is no `try/catch`, no Express error-handling middleware, and no handler for unhandled rejections. A single thrown error in any future handler will crash the process or leak a stack trace.

**Add at the bottom of the middleware chain (after all routes):**
```js
