For any Express app exposed beyond localhost, these are baseline:

| Concern | Fix |
|---|---|
| Missing security headers (XSS, clickjacking, MIME sniffing) | `app.use(helmet())` |
| No rate limiting → brute force / DoS | `express-rate-limit` on sensitive routes |
| CORS unconfigured → either broken for clients or wide open | `cors({ origin: allowlist })` — don't use `*` with credentials |
| HTTP Parameter Pollution | `hpp()` middleware |
| Compression side channels | Only enable `compression()` for non-sensitive responses |

