**Location:** lines 12–15

Email addresses (`alice@example.com`, `bob@example.com`) are hardcoded. These are RFC 2606 reserved example domains, so this is not a real data leak, but production code often drifts from this pattern. If this were real user data, it would be an A02 (Cryptographic Failures) / A08 (Data Integrity) concern.

